Dutch Farmers Losing $73 Million a Week on E. Coli, FT Reports

-- B y   R a c h e l   G r a h a m
-- 
2011-06-04T08:38:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-04/dutch-farmers-losing-73-million-a-week-on-e-coli-ft-reports.html
The E. coli outbreak in  Europe , which
has killed at least 18 people, is costing Dutch farmers about 50
million euros ($73 million) a week in lost exports, the
Financial Times said, citing figures from an industry
association.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rachel Graham in London at 
